<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-05-14T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-05-14T18:00:00-05:00" n="572" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d572">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">721.23/1717: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-05-14T18:00:00-05:00">May 14, 1933—6
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received May 15—9:10 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>51. Department’s telegram No. 46, May 13 [<hi rend="italic">12</hi>] 10
                            a.m. [<hi rend="italic">6 p.m.</hi>].<note n="79a" xml:id="d572fn79a">See footnote 76, <ref target="#pg_528">p. 528</ref>.</note> Lopez
                            is going to Lima in personal not official capacity (reported fully air
                            mail).</p>
                        <p>Colombian Government has accepted formula (my telegram No. 49<note n="80" xml:id="d572fn80"><hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_529">p. 529</ref>.</note>).</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>